Cloning project with git:
1) Login to your git hub account
2) Add git tool to your machine
3) For cloning with ssh:
  i) Generate a new ssh key: https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh/generating-a-new-ssh-key-and-adding-it-to-the-ssh-agent
  ii) Add the ssh public key to your github account: https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh/adding-a-new-ssh-key-to-your-github-account
  iii) Test your ssh connection: https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh/testing-your-ssh-connection
4) Copy the ssh url of the github repository and clone it in your localhost machine
